'''''X-Wing Rogue Squadron'' 1''', also labeled as '''"The Rebel Opposition, Chapter 1"''', is the first issue in the ''[[Star Wars: X-Wing Rogue Squadron]]'' series of comics. It was released [[July 1]], [[1995]] by [[Dark Horse Comics]].

==Publisher's summary==
''Wedge Antilles is a combat-hardened X-wing pilot, one of the only fliers to survive the missions against both Death Stars. After those two assignments and his post as leader of Rogue Squadron, you'd think he'd seen everything. But when he heads a rescue and retrieval for a downed man on the planet Cilpar, he finds something he'd never expected: a culture that hates the Empire... and hates the Alliance even more!''

==Plot summary==
On the unaligned agricultural planet [[Cilpar]], Wedge Antilles and the rest of Rogue Squadron engage in an intense dogfight with twelve [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter/Legends|TIE fighters]] attempting a stop a food convoy bound for [[Mrlsst/Legends|Mrlsst]]. After executing a trick move to eliminate two TIEs, [[Wes Janson/Legends|Wes Janson's]] [[X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-Wing]] is damaged and is forced to land by a creek on the surface. The rest of the team lands west of the city [[Kiidan]] as [[Tycho Celchu/Legends|Tycho Celchu]] heads after Janson.<ref name=":0">[[X-Wing Rogue Squadron 1|''X-Wing Rogue Squadron'' 1]]</ref> 

Antilles discusses the state of the war with [[Dllr Nep]] and [[Isplourrdacartha Estillo|Isplourrdacartha "Plourr" Estillo]], the latter of which suspects Janson or Celchu of being an Imperial [[Spy/Legends|spy]]. At the creek bed, Celchu rescues Janson from his downed fighter just before it explodes, though Janson's [[Limb/Legends|leg]] is broken. The two take shelter in a nearby cave, where Celchu fights off native winged creatures while nursing Janson to health.<ref name=":0" /> 

Back at the rebel hideout, Antilles and Plourr are confronted by [[Elscol Loro]] and her [[Elscol Loro's anti-Imperial organization|team]]. Loro suspects that the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] and the Empire (under local [[Moff/Legends|Moff]] [[Boren Tascl]]) are working together to usurp the legitimate government on Cilpar and takes the rebels to [[Tamarack]], a once-thriving neighborhood ruined by the ongoing [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|war]]. As they recover the hanged body of [[Gates Harnik]], a grocer who had supplied the rebels, Loro explains her suspicions, elaborating that her organization had a rebel contact that knew their location when Moff Tascl attacked. Loro orders [[Chang]] to [[Cremation/Legends|cremate]] the found bodies before they are eaten by wild [[Ronk/Legends|ronks]].<ref name=":0" /> 

[[Winter Celchu|Someone]] who appears to be [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] discovers Celchu and Janson at the cave and holds them at gunpoint. At Tamarack, Loro explains to Antilles that her [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]] companion [[Groznik]] owed a life debt to her late husband [[Throm Loro|Throm]] after he saved the Wookiee from Imperial execution; Throm died at the [[Battle of the Cliffs]] after returning to liberate Cilpar, leaving Groznik with Loro. Antilles gave a story of his own, retelling his assault on the [[Death Star II/Legends|second Death Star]] at the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]]. Loro uncovers a [[music ball]] in the ruins of her home and Nep identifies the tune as [[Starlight by Moonlight|"Starlight by Moonlight"]]. Suddenly, a cavalcade of Imperial walkers led by Moff Tascl storms the neighborhood.<ref name=":0" />

